5. Root filesystem contents (aggregated, not linked into this project's code)

   images/rootfs.cramfs and images/etc.jffs2 are built with Buildroot and
   contain, among others:

     BusyBox        — GPLv2          https://busybox.net
     uClibc-ng      — LGPLv2.1       https://uclibc-ng.org
     Dropbear SSH   — MIT-style      https://matt.ucc.asn.au/dropbear/
     wpa_supplicant — BSD-3-Clause   https://w1.fi/wpa_supplicant/
     iptables       — GPLv2          https://netfilter.org
     Lua            — MIT            https://lua.org
     curl / libcurl — curl license   https://curl.se
     Mbed TLS       — Apache-2.0     https://github.com/Mbed-TLS/mbedtls
     GNU nano       — GPLv3-or-later https://nano-editor.org
     ncurses        — X11/MIT-style  https://invisible-island.net/ncurses/

   These are separate programs aggregated on the same filesystem image, each
   distributed under its own license. Corresponding source is available from
   the upstream projects and from Buildroot, which fetches them verbatim.

   images/linux-esp32s3-native-full.bin is simply the concatenation, at their
   flash offsets, of the images above; every component keeps its own license.

